\slmult0\ltrpar\li400
{\b0\i0\fs24
Challenges of using Traditional Datacenters
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
Capital Investment (CapEx)
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
You gotta buys stuffs like location, hardware, infrastructure and construct. So, that initial cost is this. As an example, if we want to create a datacenter, we first need a building with cooling and power backup.
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
Operational Expenses (OpEx)
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
You need to pay for the electricity bills, internet connectivity and other maintenance stuffs. So, that is this one.
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
Scaling Problems
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Scaling Up
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
When the demand increases, datacenter capabilities should also increase. As an example, during new year shopping season, you may get a huge traffic. If datacenter doesn't have enough servers, website may crash.
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Scaling Down
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
Some systems doesn't need resources that much in some periods. So, we need to release some resources. Otherwise it becomes a waste.
\par\pard\plain}
