Software Applications
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Storage Systems
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
Cloud Resources
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
The same IT resources hosted in a cloud provider\u8217\'3fs infrastructure

Accessed through the internet

Eg:

Amazon Web Services
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Benefits
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Organizations can use resurces without owning the hardware
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
Essential Cloud Computing Properties (NIST)
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
On-Demand Self-Service
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
Users can create or release resources whenever needed without human interaction with the provider.
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Operations
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Provision
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
**Provision :**Reserving resources 

eg:

Starting a server
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Decommission
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
**Decommission : **Releasing resources when no longer needed
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Ways to do the operations
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Manual
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
**Manual **: Through a web dashboard
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Automated
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
**Automated : **Through APIs used by applications or scripts
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Broad Network Access
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
Cloud services are accessible over the internet from many locations and devices.
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Features
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Services distributed geographically
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Measured Service (Pay-Per-Use)
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Resource Pooling
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Rapid Elasticity
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li400
{\b0\i0\fs24
Cloud Application Stack
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li400
Cloud Systems are organized as** Layered Stack**

From Bottom to Top
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\fs20
1.Physical Hardware
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
The Foundation Layer of the cloud.
This includes:

- Servers
- Storage devices
- Network switches and routers
- Power supply and cooling system , these are located inside data centers
Basically provide raw computing power and storage
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
2.Virtual Hardware
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
Instead of directly giving physical machines to users,cloud systems create virtual versions of hardware.This is done using **hypervisor.**

## Hypervisor

Software that allows multiple VM s to run on one physical server.One physical server can host many VMs , improving resource utilization.
VM Components include :

- Virtual servers
- Virtual CPU
- Vistual RAM etc.
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
3.Operating Systems
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
OS sits on top of Virtual hardware.


eg-Microsoft windows server,Linux
Role of OS :

- Manage Hardware resources
- Provide services to applications

OS also handles:
- Caching - temp storage for faster access
- Process scheduling - deciding which program runs on CPU.
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
4.Middleware
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
Provides execution environments and supporting services for applications.Act as a bridge between OS and Applications.

eg-Application servers, DB systems, Messaging systems

Purpose: Simplify application development , Provide communication and data services.
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
5.Application Software
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
Contains actual SW used by users or other systems.Applications provide specific functionality. Run on top of middleware and OS.

eg-CRM Systems,ERP Systems
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
6.Business Processes
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
Represents how organizations use applications to run their operations.Business processes are workflows supported by SW systems.

eg-Credit approval process,Order processing,Billing

Applications automate and manage these organizational workflows
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li400
{\b0\i0\fs24
Essential Cloud Application Properties
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li600
{\b0\i0\fs24
IDEAL Properties
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Isolation
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
Cloud Applications should avoid storing state inside induvidual servers
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Stateless Design
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
Each request can be processed independently

**State(Session data or Application data) **should be stored externally in **Databases **or **Distributed Caches**
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Benefits
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Servers can be added or removed easily
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Supports elasticity
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Distribution
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
Cloud applications should be divided in to multiple components instead of a single large system
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Components Seperated Based On
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Communication Patterns
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Resource Requirements (CPU, memory)
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Functional Responsibilities
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Benefits
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Improves Scalability
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Improves Performance
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Elasticity
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
Applications should support **Dynamic Scaling**

**Dynamic Scaling - **Automatic adjustment of computing resources based on demand
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Horizontal Scaling (Scale Out)
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
Increase the number of servers to handle more workload

Eg:

Instead of using one webserver, adding five more servers to handle requests
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Benefits
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1400
{\b0\i0\fs24
Distributes workload across multiple machines
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Vertical Scaling (Scale Up)
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
Increasing the power of a single machine

Eg:

Upgrading the server from 8GB RAM =&gt; 64GB RAM
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Benefits
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1400
{\b0\i0\fs24
Improves performance of a single device to handle more workload
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Automated Management
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
Cloud systems rely heavily on **Automation**

**(**The system can **manage,monitor and adjust resources automatically** with little or no human effort**)**
\par\pard\plain}
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Automation Tasks
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Starting new virtual machines
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Adjusting server specifications
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Reconfiguring network topology
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Adding new components to handle traffic
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1000
{\b0\i0\fs24
Why Automation is needed
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li1200
{\b0\i0\fs24
Rapid elasticity requires systems to scale quickly without manual intervention
}
\par\pard\plain
\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
{\b0\i0\fs24
Loose Coupling
}
\par\pard\plain
{\slmult0\ltrpar\li800
Components should be independent of each other as much as possible
\par\pard\plain}
